sources.description:
Former bandit Jim Dancer becomes marshal of a Kansas town and cleans up the criminal element--with help from an old pal, Jesse James.

Fighting Man of the Plains is a 1949 American Western film  directed by Edwin L. Marin. 

Main cast:
Randolph Scott - Jim Dancer
Bill Williams - Johnny Tancred
Victor Jory - Dave Oldham
Jane Nigh - Florence Peel
Joan Taylor - Evelyn Slocum
Dale Robertson - Jesse James

Genres: Western
Release date: November 16, 1949
Filming location: United States

B&W version: https://youtu.be/18bY6rhgeJI
